other_tests.findings: Marked hypocellularity of 25% with no megakaryocytes, granulocyte 41%, erythroid precursors 51%, lymphocytes 8%, no abnormal cellular collection seen, and no evidence of myelodysplastic syndrome or malignancy.
Three copies of chromosome X in all metaphases examined.

other_tests.procedure_name: Myelodysplastic syndrome/bone marrow failure FISH panel genetic testing
other_tests.findings: An uncertain variant in two genes associated with bone marrow failure, but the clinical significance of this specific genetic change is unknown.
Did not match any of her family members.
